The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Kent hope to retain Ford

London: Kent County Cricket Club hope to retain the services of their director of cricket Graham Ford, who has been offered the coachs job of Indian team. 

The county side has said they will discuss with Ford about his future only after their penultimate group match in the Friends Provident Trophy against Hampshire on Sunday. 

Incidentally, Kent lost by two runs. 

Discussions with Ford will take place after the match. It is hoped that the popular South African will remain at Canterbury to continue the progress made towards re-establishing Kent as a major force, a statement said on Sunday. (PTI) 




